<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_DbOpenAccess.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_DbOpenAccess.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_DbOpenAccess.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_DbOpenAccess.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - A1 - Metadata - Database declares open access conditions"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_A1_FS_DbOpenAccess"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_A1_FS_DbOpenAccess"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database declares open access conditions for its content. In FAIRsharing, this corresponds to the Data Access Condition field being set to **Open** or **Partially Open**. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the registry (e.g. FAIRsharing) record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

A1 requires that (meta)data are retrievable using a standardised communications protocol. Declaring access conditions enables users and systems to understand whether database content can be retrieved and under what restrictions. This metric evaluates whether the database declares that its content is openly or partially openly accessible. Within FAIRsharing, a resource is considered **Open** when there are no restrictions on accessing its data, for example free registration or free accessibility of data. A resource is considered **Partially Open** when access to a subset of its data is restricted, for example because of a paywall, ethical or security considerations, or data protection requirements."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/A1> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
